0143#STR0143#ALL#Print Apt with Restrictions ?
0144#STR0144#ALL#As Incapable
0145#STR0145#ALL#No change
0146#STR0146#ALL#The paragraph "e" of item 7.4.4.3. of NR7 (Program of Medical Control of Occupational Health) defines that the ASO must 
0147#STR0147#ALL#inform whether the worker is capable or incapable for the specific role he will perform, is performing or has performed.
0148#STR0148#ALL#In conformity with paragraph ?e?, an ASO that has expression ?Capable with Restrictions? equals ?Incapable?, due to 
0149#STR0149#ALL#lack of legal anticipation on such attested condition. That is so because the legislation does not foresee this possibility. 
0150#STR0150#ALL#The law establishes that an employee is capable or incapable, that is, either he can work or he cannot, there is no "happy medium." 
0151#STR0151#ALL#This ambiguity may cause the company a notification or a fine.
0152#STR0152#ALL#Question 10 applies when employee is "Capable with Restriction." 
0153#STR0153#ALL#If you choose option "1-as Incapable," "Capable with Restriction" will be printed as "Incapable," 
0154#STR0154#ALL#strictly complying with item 7.4.4.3. of the NR7. 
0155#STR0155#ALL#When option "2-no changes" is chosen, "Capable with Restrictions" is printed exactly as defined.
